Dynamically adding children to <g> or <svg> elements is not working for node 
that are not ELEMENT_NODE, like comments. A ClassCastException is fired.

This is due to the handling of child insertion in the SVGGElementBridge which 
assumes that the child added is an node of type ELEMENT.
Here is a possible patch :

    /**
     * Invoked when an MutationEvent of type 'DOMNodeInserted' is fired.
     */
    public void handleDOMNodeInsertedEvent(MutationEvent evt) {
        if ( evt.getTarget().getNodeType() == Node.ELEMENT_NODE ){
            handleElementAdded((CompositeGraphicsNode)node, 
                               e, 
                               (Element)evt.getTarget());
        }
    }
